                .decptext.text-start
                    p.lead The Higher Technical Vocational Courses (CTeSP) are the new typology of short-term Higher Education training. The completion of a CTeSP confers a Higher Professional Technician Diploma, a level 5 qualification of the National Qualifications Framework. A CTeSP has 120 credits and a duration of four academic semesters, with the last semester being carried out in a work context.
                    p.lead Holders of a Higher Professional Technician Diploma can continue their Bachelor's studies, through a special access competition.
                    p.lead.fw-bold The following can apply for registration in a CTeSP:
                    p.lead a) Holders of a secondary education course or legally equivalent qualification;
                    p.lead b) Those who have passed the specially appropriate tests designed to assess the ability to attend higher education of those over 23 years of age, carried out for the course in question;
                    p.lead c) Holders of a technological specialization diploma, a higher professional technician diploma or a higher education degree who wish to requalify professionally.
